sql:
SELECT s.simulation_name, l.location_name, s.start_date
FROM simulations s
JOIN locations l ON s.location_id = l.location_id;

SELECT simulation_name, start_date, end_date
FROM simulations
ORDER BY start_date DESC;

SELECT maturity_days_after_sowing
FROM phenology
WHERE simulation_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "turned the fields of grain into a verdant sea of gold" refers to simulations where crops have yielded highly;
- The phrase "how lush are these seas" refers to the average yield of crops in grams per plant;
- The ranking from "most bountiful to the least" corresponds to sorting the average yields in descending order.

sql:
SELECT MAX(avg_yield) AS max_average_yield
FROM (
    SELECT AVG(yield) AS avg_yield
    FROM yield_data
    GROUP BY simulation_id
) AS yield_avg;

SELECT simulations.simulation_name, crops.crop_name
FROM simulations
INNER JOIN crops ON simulations.crop_id = crops.crop_id;

external_knowledge:
- "golden harvest" is a metaphorical expression referring to the yield;
- "noble grain" is a metaphorical expression referring to Wheat;
- "cultivated plots" refer to the different simulations.

